The article discusses the Trump administration's stance on immigration and refugees. It emphasizes the importance of maintaining strong borders for security and advocates for a responsible approach to refugees that prioritizes their eventual return to their home countries. President Trump has set an annual cap for refugees entering the US to ensure the safety of American citizens. The article also argues that resettling refugees in their region of origin is a better policy to alleviate financial strain on Americans. However, it highlights that the US remains a leader in global refugee efforts, both in terms of financial contributions and resettlement.